# NGC — GitHub Pages for all projects

**Policy (Ryan, 2026-07-11):** Always use **GitHub Pages** for opening any project.  
**Clarification:** **Each project must have its own Pages link** — do not hand Ryan only the site root or bury a standalone tool inside another app’s nav.

## Canonical URLs

| Item | Value |
|------|-------|
| **Projects hub** | https://ngc4160.github.io/NGC-Brain/projects/ |
| **Per-project pattern** | `https://ngc4160.github.io/NGC-Brain/projects/<slug>/` |
| **Repo** | `NGC4160/NGC-Brain` |
| **Pages source** | `gh-pages` branch |
| **Source files** | `pages/projects/<slug>/` |

## Required behavior

When building, updating, or handing off any **openable** project (dashboard, form, checklist, tool, landing page, preview):

1. **Give it a dedicated slug** under `/projects/<slug>/` (stable, kebab-case)
2. **Ship that URL** as the primary open link — not `localhost`, not `file://`, not “open the dashboard and click …”
3. Add/update `pages/projects/<slug>/index.html` (+ assets), hub `pages/projects/index.html`, and `pages/projects/projects.json`
4. Publish with `./scripts/pages/publish_projects.sh` (or equivalent) and **verify HTTP 200**
5. Update [`knowledge/06_systems/github_pages_projects.md`](knowledge/06_systems/github_pages_projects.md)
6. Tell Ryan the **project-specific** URL

Dashboard **modules** (jobs, invoicing, inventory routes inside the SPA) can stay as app routes. **Standalone projects** (forms, boards, separate tools) get their own `/projects/<slug>/` link.

## Do not

- Share only `https://ngc4160.github.io/NGC-Brain/` when the ask was for a specific tool
- Leave a project only in a PR branch / local HTML without a `/projects/<slug>/` URL
- Host NGC shop tools on a different public host unless Ryan explicitly asks
- Reuse another project’s URL for a new tool

Local `npm run dev` is fine for agent development. Handoff = **that project’s Pages URL**.

